    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the FEA modeling framework achieves High assurance for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending behavior of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. All 13 V&V 40 factors have been assessed; 12 of 13 meet or exceed their required levels. The single gap in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is considered acceptable given the strong output comparison results (all E/uval < 1.96) and the conservative nature of the single ASTM F1717 test condition. The declared High assurance level reflects the overall strength of the evidence package.",
